{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-07",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_07_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 7 - G in the Air",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 7,
  "page_start_sec": 505.84,
  "page_end_sec": 746.4,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.735,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 505.84,
      "end": 507.04,
      "text": "How perfectly fascinating,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 507.46,
      "end": 509.12,
      "text": "Bridget O'Shaughnessy said."
    },
    {
      "start": 510.14,
      "end": 511.96,
      "text": "She left her chair and stood in front of him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 512.04,
      "end": 512.4,
      "text": "close."
    },
    {
      "start": 512.7,
      "end": 514.86,
      "text": "Her eyes were wide and deep."
    },
    {
      "start": 516.22,
      "end": 518.3,
      "text": "I don't have to tell you how utterly at a",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 518.3,
      "end": 520.08,
      "text": "disadvantage you'll have me with him here"
    },
    {
      "start": 520.32,
      "end": 520.8,
      "text": "if you choose.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 522.4,
      "end": 525.08,
      "text": "Spade smiled slightly without separating his lips.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 526.12,
      "end": 526.56,
      "text": "\"'No,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 526.56,
      "end": 529.06,
      "text": "you don't have to tell me that,' he agreed."
    },
    {
      "start": 530.5,
      "end": 532.84,
      "text": "\"'And you know I'd never have placed myself in",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 532.84,
      "end": 535.39,
      "text": "this position if I hadn't trusted you completely.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 535.92,
      "end": 539.5,
      "text": "Her thumb and finger twisted a black button on his blue coat."
    },
    {
      "start": 540.8,
      "end": 541.38,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 541.56,
      "end": 544.42,
      "text": "\"'That again,' with mock resignation."
    },
    {
      "start": 545.824,
      "end": 548.02,
      "text": "\"'But you know it so,' she insisted.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 548.22,
      "end": 548.22,
      "text": "it."
    },
    {
      "start": 548.74,
      "end": 549.12,
      "text": "No,"
    },
    {
      "start": 549.24,
      "end": 552.9,
      "text": "I don't know it.\" He patted the hand that was twisting the"
    },
    {
      "start": 553.0,
      "end": 553.12,
      "text": "button."
    },
    {
      "start": 554.78,
      "end": 557.7,
      "text": "\"'My asking for reasons why I should trust you brought us here.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 558.06,
      "end": 558.66,
      "text": "Don't"
    },
    {
      "start": 558.74,
      "end": 559.94,
      "text": "let's get ourselves confused."
    },
    {
      "start": 561.0,
      "end": 562.42,
      "text": "You don't have to trust me anyway,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 562.64,
      "end": 563.12,
      "text": "as long"
    },
    {
      "start": 563.24,
      "end": 565.376,
      "text": "as you can persuade me to trust you.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 566.8,
      "end": 567.98,
      "text": "She studied his face,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 568.48,
      "end": 569.68,
      "text": "her nostrils quivered."
    },
    {
      "start": 570.56,
      "end": 571.22,
      "text": "Spade laughed.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 571.98,
      "end": 573.5,
      "text": "He patted her hand again and said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 574.4,
      "end": 575.54,
      "text": "Don't worry about that now.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 575.98,
      "end": 577.5,
      "text": "He'll be here in a moment."
    },
    {
      "start": 578.07,
      "end": 579.82,
      "text": "Get your business with him over,"
    },
    {
      "start": 579.96,
      "end": 581.36,
      "text": "and then we'll see how we stand."
    },
    {
      "start": 583.06,
      "end": 585.14,
      "text": "And you'll let me go about it in my own way?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 586.04,
      "end": 586.48,
      "text": "Of course.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 587.74,
      "end": 590.66,
      "text": "She turned her hand under his so that her fingers pressed his.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 591.78,
      "end": 592.62,
      "text": "She said softly,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 593.728,
      "end": 594.6,
      "text": "You're a godsend,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 594.68,
      "end": 596.16,
      "text": "Spade said."
    },
    {
      "start": 596.42,
      "end": 597.78,
      "text": "Don't overdo it."
    },
    {
      "start": 598.88,
      "end": 600.3,
      "text": "She looked reproachfully at him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 600.34,
      "end": 600.92,
      "text": "though smiling,"
    },
    {
      "start": 601.38,
      "end": 602.98,
      "text": "and returned to the padded rocker."
    },
    {
      "start": 605.12,
      "end": 606.32,
      "text": "Joel Cairo was excited.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 607.16,
      "end": 608.96,
      "text": "His dark eyes seemed all irises,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 609.34,
      "end": 610.16,
      "text": "and his high-pitched,"
    },
    {
      "start": 610.32,
      "end": 612.14,
      "text": "thin-voiced words were tumbling out"
    },
    {
      "start": 612.14,
      "end": 613.9,
      "text": "before Spade had got the door half"
    },
    {
      "start": 614.04,
      "end": 614.26,
      "text": "open."
    },
    {
      "start": 615.66,
      "end": 617.46,
      "text": "\"'That boy is out there watching the house,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 617.56,
      "end": 617.76,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 617.84,
      "end": 618.18,
      "text": "Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 618.3,
      "end": 619.94,
      "text": "That boy you showed me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 620.08,
      "end": 621.54,
      "text": "or to whom you showed me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 621.6,
      "end": 622.56,
      "text": "in front of the theatre."
    },
    {
      "start": 623.86,
      "end": 625.46,
      "text": "What am I to understand from that,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 625.5,
      "end": 625.72,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 625.78,
      "end": 626.14,
      "text": "Spade?"
    },
    {
      "start": 626.72,
      "end": 628.04,
      "text": "I came here in good faith,"
    },
    {
      "start": 628.18,
      "end": 630.14,
      "text": "with no thought of tricks or traps.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 630.2,
      "end": 630.34,
      "text": "hopes.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 630.82,
      "end": 634.68,
      "text": "\"'You were asked in good faith,' Spade frowned thoughtfully."
    },
    {
      "start": 635.84,
      "end": 638.34,
      "text": "\"'But I ought to have guessed that he might show up.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 639.14,
      "end": 639.8,
      "text": "He saw you come",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 639.98,
      "end": 640.12,
      "text": "in?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 640.37,
      "end": 641.22,
      "text": "\"'Naturally."
    },
    {
      "start": 641.52,
      "end": 642.9,
      "text": "I could have gone on,"
    },
    {
      "start": 643.0,
      "end": 644.84,
      "text": "but that seemed pointless since you"
    },
    {
      "start": 644.84,
      "end": 646.83,
      "text": "had already let him see us together.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 648.288,
      "end": 651.76,
      "text": "Bridget O'Shaughnessy came into the passageway behind Spade and asked",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 651.9,
      "end": 652.22,
      "text": "anxiously,"
    },
    {
      "start": 652.63,
      "end": 653.38,
      "text": "\"'What,"
    },
    {
      "start": 653.42,
      "end": 653.72,
      "text": "boy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 653.84,
      "end": 654.84,
      "text": "what is it?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 656.544,
      "end": 658.56,
      "text": "Cairo removed his black hat from his head,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 658.74,
      "end": 659.7,
      "text": "bowed stiffly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 659.74,
      "end": 661.04,
      "text": "and said in a prim voice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 662.26,
      "end": 663.16,
      "text": "\"'If you do not know,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 663.32,
      "end": 664.04,
      "text": "ask Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 664.16,
      "end": 664.48,
      "text": "Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 665.2,
      "end": 667.68,
      "text": "I know nothing about it except through him.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 668.92,
      "end": 671.72,
      "text": "\"'A kid who's been trying to tail me around town all evening,'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 672.288,
      "end": 673.68,
      "text": "Spade spoke carelessly over"
    },
    {
      "start": 673.68,
      "end": 674.14,
      "text": "his shoulder,"
    },
    {
      "start": 674.26,
      "end": 675.78,
      "text": "not turning to face the girl."
    },
    {
      "start": 677.06,
      "end": 677.54,
      "text": "\"'Come on in,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 677.6,
      "end": 677.88,
      "text": "Cairo."
    },
    {
      "start": 678.74,
      "end": 679.96,
      "text": "There's no use standing",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 680.22,
      "end": 681.88,
      "text": "here talking for all the neighbors.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 683.008,
      "end": 684.78,
      "text": "Brigid O'Shaughnessy grasped Spade's",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 684.78,
      "end": 686.28,
      "text": "arm above the elbow and demanded,"
    },
    {
      "start": 687.2,
      "end": 688.52,
      "text": "\"'Did he follow you to my apartment?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 689.2,
      "end": 689.8,
      "text": "\"'No."
    },
    {
      "start": 689.82,
      "end": 691.14,
      "text": "I shook him before that."
    },
    {
      "start": 692.34,
      "end": 694.46,
      "text": "Then I suppose he came back here to try",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 694.46,
      "end": 695.55,
      "text": "to pick me up again.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 696.57,
      "end": 697.22,
      "text": "Cairo,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 697.38,
      "end": 699.82,
      "text": "holding his black hat to his belly with both hands,"
    },
    {
      "start": 700.04,
      "end": 700.92,
      "text": "had come into"
    },
    {
      "start": 700.92,
      "end": 701.66,
      "text": "the passageway."
    },
    {
      "start": 702.72,
      "end": 705.14,
      "text": "Spade shut the corridor door behind him and they went",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 705.14,
      "end": 705.92,
      "text": "into the living room."
    },
    {
      "start": 706.86,
      "end": 709.78,
      "text": "There Cairo bowed stiffly over his hat once more",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 709.96,
      "end": 710.24,
      "text": "and said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 711.42,
      "end": 713.04,
      "text": "\"'I am delighted to see you again,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 713.14,
      "end": 713.87,
      "text": "Miss O'Shaughnessy.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 715.3,
      "end": 716.4,
      "text": "\"'I was sure you would be,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 716.52,
      "end": 717.74,
      "text": "Joe,' she replied,"
    },
    {
      "start": 717.92,
      "end": 719.02,
      "text": "giving him her hand."
    },
    {
      "start": 719.44,
      "end": 721.12,
      "text": "He made a formal bow"
    },
    {
      "start": 721.12,
      "end": 722.76,
      "text": "over it and released it quickly."
    },
    {
      "start": 724.04,
      "end": 726.58,
      "text": "She sat in the padded rocker she had occupied before.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 727.552,
      "end": 729.4,
      "text": "Cairo sat in the armchair by the table.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 729.92,
      "end": 730.7,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 730.78,
      "end": 732.94,
      "text": "when he had hung Cairo's hat and coat in the"
    },
    {
      "start": 732.98,
      "end": 733.3,
      "text": "closet,"
    },
    {
      "start": 733.54,
      "end": 735.96,
      "text": "sat on an end of the sofa in front of the"
    },
    {
      "start": 735.96,
      "end": 737.62,
      "text": "windows and began to roll a cigarette."
    },
    {
      "start": 739.136,
      "end": 740.7,
      "text": "Bridget O'Shaughnessy said to Cairo,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 741.94,
      "end": 743.94,
      "text": "Sam told me about your offer for the Falcon.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 744.84,
      "end": 746.4,
      "text": "How soon can you have the money ready?",
      "para_break": true
    }
  ]
}